            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="Shock waves and Science of Nano Materials:"
            android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
            android:textSize="16dp"
            android:textStyle="bold"
            android:layout_below="@+id/text25"
            android:id="@+id/text26" />

        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="Definition of Mach number, distinctions between- acoustic, ultrasonic, subsonic and supersonic waves. Description of a shock wave and its applications. Basics of conservation of mass, momentum and energy. Normal shock equations (Rankine-Hugonit equations). Method of creating shock waves in the laboratory using a shock tube, description of hand operated Reddy shock tube and its characteristics.\nIntroduction to Nano Science,  Density of states in 1D, 2D and 3D structures. Synthesis : Top–down and Bottom–up approach, Ball Milling and Sol–Gel methods.\nCNT – Properties, synthesis: Arc discharge, Pyrolysis methods,Applications.\nScanning Electron microscope: Principle, working and applications.\n

                                               *****"
            android:layout_marginTop="2dp"
            android:textSize="15dp"
            android:layout_below="@+id/text26"
            android:id="@+id/text27" />

